<p>

If I were to do a “paleo” diet, I would do a pre-Hispanic (before the arrival of the Spanish) Mexican diet.  To wit:

<p>

<ul>
<li> Corn
<li> Beans
<li> Peanuts (originally from Peru, but were in Mexico by the time Cortéz showed up to liberate the Tlaxcaltecas from the Aztecs)
<li> Turkey (but, as it turns out, not chicken)
<li> Chocolate 
<li> Avocado
<li> Tomatoes
<li> Nopales (an exotic Mexican edible cactus leaf)
<li> Huazotle (an even more exotic Mexican seed)
<li> Honey (this appears to be the only pre-Hispanic refined sugar, Piloncillo uses post-Hispanic cane sugar)
</ul>

